      • defaultDomainKey

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder defaultDomainKey(String defaultDomainKey)
        If specified, indicates the default domain that should be selected. By default this means that the WebCmsSiteConfigurationFilter will select this domain if no other has matched.
        Returns:
        this.

      • noDomainAllowed

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder noDomainAllowed(boolean noDomainAllowed)
        Is a no-domain configuration level possible? If set to false, a domain-bound entity will always require a specific domain to be set.

        When set to false, calls to WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.isNoDomainAllowed(Class) will always return false for domain-bound entities.

        Returns:
        this.

      • disabled

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder disabled(boolean disabled)
        If disabled, no multi-domain configuration is active. If a default domain is specified, it will still be applied.
        Returns:
        this.

      • domainSelectablePerEntity

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder domainSelectablePerEntity(boolean domainSelectablePerEntity)
        Can the domain be selected per entity or not. If false (the default), a domain will be selected on a top-level and the management UI will scope itself only to objects of that domain.

        Only relevant if the administration UI is active.

        Returns:
        this.

      • metadataClass

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder metadataClass(Class<? extends WebCmsDomainAware> metadataClass)
        The actual metadata implementation that should be used for the domains. If specified, metadata instances will be created as prototype beans and attached to the domain context for their corresponding domain. Metadata must implement the WebCmsDomainAware interface.

        If null, no metadata will be loaded for domains.

        Returns:
        this.

      • noDomainMetadataBeanName

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder noDomainMetadataBeanName(String noDomainMetadataBeanName)
        Name of the bean that should be retrieved if the no-domain context is loaded. Because no-domain does not correspond with a WebCmsDomain instance, metadata for no-domain will only be loaded if a bean name is specified.

        The actual bean returned can be a singleton and is not required to implement WebCmsDomainAware. Even if it would, WebCmsDomainAware.setWebCmsDomain(WebCmsDomain) would never be called.

        Returns:
        this.

      • domainContextFilterClass

        public WebCmsMultiDomainConfiguration.WebCmsMultiDomainConfigurationBuilder domainContextFilterClass(Class<? extends AbstractWebCmsDomainContextFilter> domainContextFilterClass)
        Implementation of a AbstractWebCmsDomainContextFilter that is responsible for determining the WebCmsDomainContext for incoming web requests. If a class is set, the bean will be retrieved and configured as a servlet filter for all requests.
        Returns:
        this.
